atus=in_progress and asserts only descriptor-level evidence, so there is no over-claim to refute. The marketplace source (registry.js, validators.js, states.js, index.js, model.js), the contract JSON, the validation script, and the tests are internally consistent and fail-closed. The CP853 binding (registry.js:190-205) and requirements (registry.js:674-714) match the planned 40-unit distribution exactly (implementation 16 / test 8 / ui 4 / security_audit 4 / failure_recovery 4 / contract 2 / claude_review 2; micro-titles Test-And-Golden-Case 10 / Hermes 22 / Claude-Review 8; micro-phases M07=10/M08=22/M09=8), and the manifest's 40 included_units sum identically; the case set row_count is 40 (registry.js:911). validateMarketplaceCp853EvidenceReviewPacketDescriptor (validators.js:1063-1131) enforces per-row descriptor_only + runtime_execution=false and rejects connector secrets, OAuth tokens, prompt/completion payloads, real client data, permission-decision detail, audit bodies, marketplace runtime opening, and permission/audit/product-state writes; MARKETPLACE_NO_WRITE_ATTESTATION (registry.js:35-52) is mirrored into the descriptor and contract projection, and deepFreeze (registry.js:4-10) makes descriptors immutable. The validation script (scripts/validate-rp28-marketplace-custom-ai-apps-contract.mjs) is read-only (readFile + validators + exit code; no writes). Authority boundaries hold: Claude is read-only and explicitly not final approver (claude_is_final_approval=false, claude_packet.read_only=true, promotes_claude_to_final_approval=false), human approval is required for runtime opening (deferred to next pack CP00-854 via runtime_opening_pack_id), Hermes is a deterministic evidence/receipt descriptor only (emits_runtime_receipt=false, writes_product_state=false, no_real_data=true) and not embedded in product runtime, and local_validation_claims_enterprise_trust=false. CP178+ review hardening is correctly applied: the primary review-receipt.json is itself an infra