0:control-plane:validate, git diff --check) have not been executed. This matches the pack's documented sequence (full validation runs after exactly one valid hardened read-only Claude review and queue regeneration), so it is not a defect in the descriptor evidence, but it is a genuine outstanding gate before production_ready can be flipped to true.","recommendation":"Keep the production_ready=true flip gated on the full 10-command validation suite passing after this valid review receipt is recorded; do not close out on the review verdict alone.","post_review_disposition":"Non-blocking for this read-only review; closeout remains independently conditional on the harness running the full suite post-review (enforced via gate_outcome)."},{"id":"CP853-R-02","severity":"P3","title":"Primary review receipt currently holds an invalid (API 500) review; one valid receipt must be persisted before closeout","file":"artifacts/closeout-pack-claude-review/cp00-853/review-receipt.json","line":5,"details":"review-receipt.json status is invalid_review / valid_review=false / closeout_eligible=false (api_error_status 500, parsed_review null), and manifest.json valid_review_receipts is empty with exactly_one_valid_pack_review_required=true. The hardening correctly refuses to count this failed execution, and review_adjudication.finding_counts / construction-inspection.claude_findings are still null pending a valid review. Closeout requires persisting exactly one valid hardened read-only review receipt (this review) and updating manifest.valid_review_receipts and the adjudication/inspection finding_counts from null to the recorded values.","recommendation":"Persist this valid review as the single accepted pack-level review receipt, keep the prior failed executions quarantined, and flip the manifest/adjudication/inspection finding_counts from null to the reported P0/P1/P2/P3 values.","post_review_disposition":"Expected next step in the documented sequence; correctly gated and non-blocking f